The Governor- elect of Zamfara State, Alhaji Mukhtar Shehu Idris, has urged members of the opposition parties in the state to join hands with him to move the state forward. Addressing newsmen shortly after he was declared winner of the state governorship election Alhaji Mukhtar Idris also called on contestants from other parties to accept the outcome of the election in good faith adding that they were all winners in the political process. He said their political aspiration was not greater than the collective will of the people of the state and, therefore they should place the interest of their people above all other considerations. “My victory has emboldened my resolve to dedicate myself to serve our good people. I assure you that my administration will work right from day one for a more prosperous Zamfara state,” he added. Alhaji Mukhtar Idris further said he appreciated the weight of responsibility bestowed on him and he has taken his new challenge with every sense of responsibility.  Primaries: Sacked Zamfara APC declares Idris, Yari winners As uncertainty dogs Zamfara APC: Mutawalle, Dansadau, Shinkafi, Adamu fight for guber seat BREAKING: INEC bans APC from fielding candidates in Zamfara